  "text": "Although the FBA only returns a single flux distribution, the constraints imposed on the system under investigation do not always allow to obtain a unique solution, but may confine the solution space to a feasible set of alternative optimal flux distributions in which the same optimal flux value of the objective function may be reached through different but equally possible ways. In this context, the Flux Variability Analysis (FVA) [CITATION_1] returns the range of flux variability of each reaction, i.e. the allowable minimum and the maximum fluxes by each model reaction.",
